Package: MTTK
Title: Metatranscriptomics toolkit for nested gene, genome, and community analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person(
        given = "Antton",
        family = "Alberdi",
        email = "antton.alberdi@sund.ku.dk",
        role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
Author: Antton Alberdi [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Antton Alberdi <antton.alberdi@sund.ku.dk>
Description: MTTK helps users organize genome-resolved
    metatranscriptomic studies as linked gene, genome, and community data. It
    stores count and abundance assays together with sample information, genome
    annotations, and mappings across biological and functional hierarchies in
    Bioconductor-friendly containers. This makes it easier to summarize
    features, compare genomes or clades, and prepare data for downstream
    differential expression, association analysis, aggregation, and
    visualization workflows.
